snippet.textDisplay: 21:50 really got to me, because i can relate. i was in a bad place mentally for a while, didnt care about much of anything, only felt depressed, etc. etc. then i discovered the miata, and ended up buying my own. since then its truly given me something to care about. i have so many plans for this car, and it really pulled me out of a dark place. i will eternally be grateful for this car currently sitting in my driveway. every time i see it, it fills me with an emotion i didnt know i could feel. even now, while it doesnt run and needs an engine rebuild, i still care deeply about it. i know it would make more logical sense to dump it and buy another one, but this car did so much for me and will always hold sentimental value.
snippet.textOriginal: 21:50 really got to me, because i can relate. i was in a bad place mentally for a while, didnt care about much of anything, only felt depressed, etc. etc. then i discovered the miata, and ended up buying my own. since then its truly given me something to care about. i have so many plans for this car, and it really pulled me out of a dark place. i will eternally be grateful for this car currently sitting in my driveway. every time i see it, it fills me with an emotion i didnt know i could feel. even now, while it doesnt run and needs an engine rebuild, i still care deeply about it. i know it would make more logical sense to dump it and buy another one, but this car did so much for me and will always hold sentimental value.

I bought my own car, and I would love to make a film about it with you guys. It's s project, it's a lot of work, but it's so much fun. I'm pretty sure you guys will definitely like it. I hope to "finish" it around summer next year. Well, finish all the plans I have right now. It;s so much more then just a car. It's something I genuinly love and adore. Keep up the good work. Thankyou very much, Pim.
